episodes.title: Epstein Files Mystery Deepens: Virginia Giuffre’s Family Demands Full Release | Trump–Epstein | LIVE
episodes.description:
The mystery surrounding Jeffrey Epstein deepens as the family of Virginia Giuffre—one of Epstein’s most prominent sex-trafficking accusers—demands the immediate release of all Epstein files. Speaking to CNN’s Kaitlan Collins, Giuffre’s family says that Virginia wanted the truth to come out and that sealed documents continue to protect powerful individuals connected to Epstein’s global network.

Giuffre’s brother makes an emotional appeal, stating that she was “not an object,” but someone who was “stolen” and “preyed upon.” While Epstein died in jail in 2019 before facing trial, questions around his associates, flight logs, sealed testimonies, and elite connections remain unanswered.

The renewed calls for transparency have once again brought attention to Epstein’s past links with influential figures, including former US President Donald Trump and his Mar-a-Lago association. While Trump has denied any wrongdoing and no criminal charges have been proven, the family insists the focus should remain on truth, accountability, and justice for survivors.

As pressure mounts globally, the key question remains: If there is nothing to hide, why are the Epstein files still sealed?
Watch this report for the latest updates, context, and global reactions.

episodes.title: Virginia Giuffre’s Family Reacts After Prince Andrew Is Stripped of Royal Title | Buckingham Palace
episodes.description:
LONDON, UK — The family of Virginia Giuffre has spoken out after King Charles officially stripped Prince Andrew of his royal title and privileges amid renewed public scrutiny over his alleged ties to Jeffrey Epstein.

The move marks a historic moment for the British monarchy, as Buckingham Palace distances itself from long-standing controversy. Giuffre’s family welcomed the decision, calling it “a small step toward accountability,” while royal watchers say it could permanently alter Andrew’s standing within the royal family.
